      "solution": "import re\n\nitem_prices = {\n    \"S\": 1200,\n    \"s\": 508,\n    \"L\": 157000,\n    \"G\": 1000,\n    \"E\": 12200,\n    \"H\": 469,\n    \"B\": 337,\n    \"k\": 10,\n}\n\nitems = input()\nprice = sum(\n    int(match[1]) * item_prices[match[2]]\n    for match in re.finditer(r\"([0-9]+)([A-Za-z])\", items)\n)\n\nprint(price)",
      "statement": "You have won a fight in RPG 3000, and have earned some loot! You are about to sell it, and would like to estimate the earnings.\n\nThe loot will be provided in concatenated groups of a quantity and an item, represented as a letter among the following:\n\n* {{S}} (skull): $1200\n* {{s}} (spleen): $508\n* {{L}} (liver): $157000\n* {{G}} (gallblader): $1000\n* {{E}} (eye): $12200\n* {{H}} (shoulder): $469\n* {{B}} (pint of blood): $337\n* {{k}} (inch of skin): $10\n\nFor example, {{1S2E}} represents 1 skull and 2 eyes, which will be worth {{1 * 1200 + 2 * 12200 = 25600}}.\n\nNote that a quantity can be {{0}}, and that there can be multiple quantities for the same kind of items.",
