    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">You have won a fight in RPG 3000, and have earned some loot! You are about to sell it, and would like to estimate the earnings.<br><br>The loot will be provided in concatenated groups of a quantity and an item, represented as a letter among the following:<br><br>* <const>S</const> (skull): $1200<br>* <const>s</const> (spleen): $508<br>* <const>L</const> (liver): $157000<br>* <const>G</const> (gallblader): $1000<br>* <const>E</const> (eye): $12200<br>* <const>H</const> (shoulder): $469<br>* <const>B</const> (pint of blood): $337<br>* <const>k</const> (inch of skin): $10<br><br>For example, <const>1S2E</const> represents 1 skull and 2 eyes, which will be worth <const>1 * 1200 + 2 * 12200 = 25600</const>.<br><br>Note that a quantity can be <const>0</const>, and that there can be multiple quantities for the same kind of items.</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>First line:</strong> <var>items</var>, in the format described above.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\"><strong>First line:</strong> Obtained total price.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\"><const>2 &lt;= length(</const><var>items</var><const>) &lt; 99</const></div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">2S</pre>\n         </div>\